reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 17, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This is a great mattress with a great price tag. Very comfortable (5'5" 155 pounds), soft but not flimsy at all. It opened up to full form in a short amount of time and we were able to put it on the bed and make it up shortly after opening it. Its a bit heavy but so much easier to get up to the 2nd floor because it comes compacted in a smaller box. Shipping was fast, price was fair...definitely would purchase again and highly recommend

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 6, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Dont overthink it
reviews.reviewText: I was nervous about buying a mattress online but this one came out good. It's a decent price, and it is so comfy. You have to wait a few days for it to fluff up, but it shipped quickly and came in great quality.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Never fully inflated; but it’s fine otherwise.
reviews.reviewText: If you want a 10” bed, I suggest ordering the 12”. I ordered a 10”, and left it on the frame for at least 4 days before anyone was even allowed to enter the room. Lol. But it still never fully rose (see pic). It’s about a month and a half later now. It’s still only 8”. But it’s fine. It’s comfortable, it hasn’t lost its form in any area, and it serves its purpose. I don’t regret the purchase. Just order a size up from what you really want. Oh, and it inflated almost immediately. Like, I had to step back because I didn’t expect it to inflate that quickly. But we still didn’t touch it for several days. Also, there was no smell at all. Everything was great except the 2” loss.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 6, 2024
reviews.reviewText: What a great full-sized mattress. It is firm but soft. Set up in less than 10 seconds once the wrapping was cut open (popped out of the plastic quickly so be prepared), and was ready to use in 3 days. I don't understand some of the complaints about it being noisey. Its a typical mattress. It makes mattress noises. Great value. I'm very impressed.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 6, 2024
reviews.reviewText: What a fantastic mattress at such a reasonable price. I honestly didn't expect it to be this good. It's a true king size and firm but soft. I'm 36 years old with a few old sports injuries, I used to wake up with aching hips and a kink in my neck, but with this mattress I've had the best sleep of my life and zero pain. We've had it for about six months now. Zero complaints.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 19, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Honestly I love it, it’s affordable and more comfortable and cozy than I would’ve thought. This is a steal for the price! I’ve been sleeping really well. Make sure you give it at least two full days to get into its shape.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Get what you pay for.
reviews.reviewText: First off, for the price, I wasn’t expecting $1000 mattress quality.Advertised as Medium Firm but it is very soft.Laying on it is comfortable enough.Advertised with extra firmness on edges.Sitting on the edge to get dressed or whatever and you sink to the frame and can feel the springs on your rear.Advertised as a 12” only rose to 10” after 24 hours. I was aware of that from other reviews so I ordered the 12” instead of a smaller one.Overall, for around $200 it’s good enough for now.
